# EVOLUTION CONCLUSION REPORT: REFACTOR & FALLBACK SIMPLIFICATION

## 1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
This iteration successfully unified the compilation execution path, eliminated structural redundancy, and introduced a robust hierarchical fallback system. Crucially, the compiler's dynamic tracking variables (flow character and debug flag) were promoted from recursive execution arguments to global runtime context members. This simplifies the compiler signatures, reduces stack overhead, and exposes a rich execution profile that can be serialized and supplied directly to downstream LLM actors as native context.

